{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783301881,"nonce":"j1fGJgQJ5sk2kG/uhjOnbMbgVRs=","title":"MySQL introspection silently drops index prefix lengths (INDEX(col(10))).","message":"The index query in `crates/squealy-mysql/src/introspect.rs` (`indexes`, `:464-518`) never selects\n`information_schema.STATISTICS.SUB_PART`, so a prefix index like `INDEX(name(10))` reads back as a\nfull-column index. Re-rendering produces a different (wider) index than the source, and the diff\ncan never converge on a DB that uses prefix indexes.\n\nThe neutral `IndexModel` has no per-column prefix-length field either, so this needs a small model\naddition (prefix length per index column) plus reading `SUB_PART` and rendering `col(n)`.\n\nFound in the introspection round-trip audit (see ~/.claude/plans/squealy-introspection-audit.md).","files":null}]}